==Latin==

===Noun===
'''nemo turpitudinem suam allegans auditur'''  {{en-noun-unc}}

# {{law}}{{archaic}}: literally "no man may [[reclaim]] what he has [[rendered]] to the [[other]] [[party]] with [[knowledge]] of the [[illegality]] of his [[performance]]"; [[common law]] principle that a person who [[contract]]ed to do an illegal act could not recover what he had paid in the performance of that act